main event: A group observed points of light in the sky on July 29, 1964.
interesting points: The observed lights were initially thought to be unusual but were later determined to be likely celestial objects., The observation lasted for approximately 3 hours and 35 minutes., Conditions were reported as clear and the objects appeared stationary., The conclusion of the sighting indicated it was classified as a known natural phenomenon., The estimated position of the objects was about 32 degrees in the eastern sky.
sighted object: points of light in the sky
